// Strict entry importing a `#relaxed` lib: the untyped-closure `Any`
// return flows into a concrete `Int` scalar value-binding slot. This is
// the value-slot mirror of the call-arg leak: under strict mode a
// value-binding slot is fail-closed against `Any`, exactly like the
// function-argument boundary, so the analyzer statically flags it with a
// `StaticTypeMismatch` (expects Int, got Any) instead of deferring to a
// runtime typed-slot check. Per-module strictness keeps the escape hatch
// open: a `#relaxed` importer (see `relaxed_any_leak.relon`) is not
// tightened. This fixture pins that the value-slot path is fail-closed.
{
    #import lib from "./any_leak_lib.relon",
    Int x: lib.blob("hello")
}
